9
00:00:23.001 --> 00:00:25.007
When you evaluate types of AI systems,

10
00:00:25.007 --> 00:00:27.006
consider the following.

11
00:00:27.006 --> 00:00:31.009
What formats of data do you need for your project?

12
00:00:31.009 --> 00:00:34.002
What would be your input data?

13
00:00:34.002 --> 00:00:36.009
What would be your desired output data?

14
00:00:36.009 --> 00:00:39.000
Different types of AI models and applications

15
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:41.007
accept and generate different formats of data,

16
00:00:41.007 --> 00:00:44.001
such as text or images.

17
00:00:44.001 --> 00:00:47.005
How often will your data need to be refreshed?

18
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:49.005
Depending on your business objective,

19
00:00:49.005 --> 00:00:53.004
data might need to be refreshed daily or weekly or monthly.

20
00:00:53.004 --> 00:00:56.005
And for some applications such as medical diagnostics,

21
00:00:56.005 --> 00:01:01.001
a continuous stream of realtime data might even be needed.

22
00:01:01.001 --> 00:01:05.003
Next, what source of high-quality data do you have at scale?

23
00:01:05.003 --> 00:01:08.004
It could be owned by you or coming through partnerships.

24
00:01:08.004 --> 00:01:11.007
Remember that the focus should be on proprietary data.

25
00:01:11.007 --> 00:01:14.000
For example, if your company is looking to use AI

26
00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.004
for pharmaceutical research or drug discovery,

27
00:01:17.004 --> 00:01:19.002
then data on molecular structures

28
00:01:19.002 --> 00:01:22.005
and biological pathways might be needed.

29
00:01:22.005 --> 00:01:25.007
So data will need to be refreshed frequently

30
00:01:25.007 --> 00:01:27.008
as new findings emerge.

31
00:01:27.008 --> 00:01:30.003
And the AI system you choose should be able

32
00:01:30.003 --> 00:01:33.009
to handle the scale, the complex interactions,

33
00:01:33.009 --> 00:01:36.003
and analyze vast quantities of data.

34
00:01:36.003 --> 00:01:39.000
Or if your company's planning to use AI

35
00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:42.002
to improve the accuracy of demand forecasting,

36
00:01:42.002 --> 00:01:44.002
then data on past sales performance,

37
00:01:44.002 --> 00:01:46.007
economic indicators, reports on industry trends

38
00:01:46.007 --> 00:01:50.002
and customer behavior might be needed.

39
00:01:50.002 --> 00:01:53.001
The system will need to assimilate large data sets

40
00:01:53.001 --> 00:01:57.002
in different formats and continuously update

41
00:01:57.002 --> 00:01:59.003
as new data becomes available

42
00:01:59.003 --> 00:02:01.002
and then generate accurate predictions

43
00:02:01.002 --> 00:02:03.004
for different products and markets.

44
