So now let's transition to the type of AI you need.

45
00:02:06.003 --> 00:02:09.009
This is basically the AI engine you want to implement.

46
00:02:09.009 --> 00:02:13.002
If your goal is to use AI to create product designs,

47
00:02:13.002 --> 00:02:16.000
you might want to use a system that has specific capabilities

48
00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:18.004
for 3D modeling or animations,

49
00:02:18.004 --> 00:02:19.008
or if you're interested in using AI

50
00:02:19.008 --> 00:02:21.006
to improve customer service,

51
00:02:21.006 --> 00:02:23.001
you might want a system that excels

52
00:02:23.001 --> 00:02:26.004
in natural language processing or chat bot development.

53
00:02:26.004 --> 00:02:30.005
Or, you might want a system design or product schema

54
00:02:30.005 --> 00:02:35.001
that is a mix of workflows and generation and automation.

55
00:02:35.001 --> 00:02:38.001
Once you have an idea of the type of system you need,

56
00:02:38.001 --> 00:02:40.008
there are three more considerations for you.

57
00:02:40.008 --> 00:02:43.001
The first one is implementation.

58
00:02:43.001 --> 00:02:45.004
How easy or difficult will it be

59
00:02:45.004 --> 00:02:48.003
to implement this type of AI in your company?

60
00:02:48.003 --> 00:02:51.005
Consider the technical resources, the personnel, the cost,

61
00:02:51.005 --> 00:02:53.004
and the time needed to integrate the model

62
00:02:53.004 --> 00:02:55.007
into your business processes.

63
00:02:55.007 --> 00:03:00.008
Second, scalability, can the model scale with your business?

64
00:03:00.008 --> 00:03:02.004
You want to choose a type of AI

65
00:03:02.004 --> 00:03:05.001
that will be able to grow with your company

66
00:03:05.001 --> 00:03:06.006
rather than becoming obsolete

67
00:03:06.006 --> 00:03:09.006
or struggling to handle the increased volume.

68
00:03:09.006 --> 00:03:12.000
And lastly, transparency.

69
00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:13.001
Are you able to understand

70
00:03:13.001 --> 00:03:15.009
how the model is making its decisions?

71
00:03:15.009 --> 00:03:19.003
Transparency is crucial for establishing trust,

72
00:03:19.003 --> 00:03:22.004
and can help you fine tune the model over time.

73
